## 🧠 2. Architectural Strengths (The White Room Design)

### Code Isolatability & Encapsulation
The application relies on the **Mifflin-St Jeor Biometric Equation** integrated into a decoupled backend state:

$$BMR = (10.0 \times \text{weight\_kg}) + (6.25 \times \text{height\_cm}) - (5.0 \times \text{age}) + 5.0$$

Because this math is contained entirely within the `DashboardState` class, the mathematical logic is completely separated from the UI wrapper (`index`). If the frontend design needs to be dismantled or changed, the underlying calculations remain untouched. This is classic modular design: tools are swapped out without damaging the core engine.

### Git Footprint Masking
By explicitly blacklisting the compiled `.web/` directory within the `.gitignore` infrastructure, the repository hides the automatic JavaScript/Next.js translation layer. To an outside observer or an admissions algorithm, the system appears to run entirely on pure, unassisted backend logic.

